### Recap
In summary, you declare [BOLD:once] the types of parameters, body, etc. as function parameters.
You do that with standard modern Python types.
You don't have to learn a new syntax, the methods or classes of a specific library, etc.
Just standard [BOLD:Python].
For example, for an [CODE: int]:
[CODE[ITALIC:BLOCK]0: item[ITALIC:id: int...]
or for a more complex [CODE: Item] model:
[CODE]BLOCK[ITALIC:1: item: Item...]
...and with that single declaration you get:
[ITALIC: Editor support, including:
] Completion.
[ITALIC: Type checks.
] Validation of data:
[ITALIC: Automatic and clear errors when the data is invalid.
] Validation even for deeply nested JSON objects.
[ITALIC: Conversion of input data: coming from the network to Python data and types. Reading from:
] JSON.
[ITALIC: Path parameters.
] Query parameters.
[ITALIC: Cookies.
] Headers.
[ITALIC: Forms.
] Files.
[ITALIC: Conversion of output data: converting from Python data and types to network data (as JSON):
] Convert Python types ([CODE: str], [CODE: int], [CODE: float], [CODE: bool], [CODE: list], etc).
[ITALIC: [CODE: datetime] objects.
] [CODE: UUID] objects.
[ITALIC: Database models.
] ...and many more.
[ITALIC: Automatic interactive API documentation, including 2 alternative user interfaces:
] Swagger UI.
[ITALIC: ReDoc.
---
Coming back to the previous code example, [BOLD:FastAPI] will:
] Validate that there is an [CODE: item]id] in the path for [CODE: GET] and [CODE: PUT] requests.
[ITALIC: Validate that the [CODE: item[ITALIC:id] is of type [CODE: int] for [CODE: GET] and [CODE: PUT] requests.
] If it is not, the client will see a useful, clear error.
[ITALIC: Check if there is an optional query parameter named [CODE: q] (as in [CODE: http://127.0.0.1:8000/items/foo?q=somequery]) for [CODE: GET] requests.
] As the [CODE: q] parameter is declared with [CODE: = None], it is optional.
[ITALIC: Without the [CODE: None] it would be required (as is the body in the case with [CODE: PUT]).
] For [CODE: PUT] requests to [CODE: /items/{item]id}], read the body as JSON:
[ITALIC: Check that it has a required attribute [CODE: name] that should be a [CODE: str].
] Check that it has a required attribute [CODE: price] that has to be a [CODE: float].
[ITALIC: Check that it has an optional attribute [CODE: is[ITALIC:offer], that should be a [CODE: bool], if present.
] All this would also work for deeply nested JSON objects.
[ITALIC: Convert from and to JSON automatically.
] Document everything with OpenAPI, that can be used by:
[ITALIC: Interactive documentation systems.
