[ITALIC: The parameter [CODE: regex] has been deprecated and replaced by [CODE: pattern].
] You can read more about it in the docs for Query Parameters and String Validations: Add regular expressions.
[ITALIC: New Pydantic models use an improved and simplified attribute [CODE: model]config] that takes a simple dict instead of an internal class [CODE: Config] for their configuration.
] You can read more about it in the docs for Declare Request Example Data.
[ITALIC: The attribute [CODE: schema[ITALIC:extra] for the internal class [CODE: Config] has been replaced by the key [CODE: json]schema[ITALIC:extra] in the new [CODE: model]config] dict.
] You can read more about it in the docs for Declare Request Example Data.
[ITALIC: When you install [CODE: "fastapi[all]"] it now also includes:
] [[CODE: pydantic-settings]](https://docs.pydantic.dev/latest/usage/pydantic[ITALIC:settings/) - for settings management.
[ITALIC: [[CODE: pydantic-extra-types]](https://docs.pydantic.dev/latest/usage/types/extra]types/extra[ITALIC:types/) - for extra types to be used with Pydantic.
