## 0.28.0 (2019-06-05)
[ITALIC: Implement dependency cache per request.
] This avoids calling each dependency multiple times for the same request.
[ITALIC: This is useful while calling external services, performing costly computation, etc.
] This also means that if a dependency was declared as a [ITALIC:path operation decorator] dependency, possibly at the router level (with [CODE: .include[ITALIC:router()]) and then it is declared again in a specific [ITALIC:path operation], the dependency will be called only once.
[ITALIC: The cache can be disabled per dependency declaration, using [CODE: use]cache=False] as in [CODE: Depends(your[ITALIC:dependency, use]cache=False)].
] Updated docs at: Using the same dependency multiple times.
[ITALIC: PR #292.
] Implement dependency overrides for testing.
[ITALIC: This allows using overrides/mocks of dependencies during tests.
] New docs: Testing Dependencies with Overrides.
- PR #291.

