## 0.22.0 (2019-05-16)
[ITALIC: Add support for [CODE: dependencies] parameter:
] A parameter in [ITALIC:path operation decorators], for dependencies that should be executed but the return value is not important or not used in the [ITALIC:path operation function].
[ITALIC: A parameter in the [CODE: .include[ITALIC:router()] method of FastAPI applications and routers, to include dependencies that should be executed in each ]path operation[ITALIC: in a router.
] This is useful, for example, to require authentication or permissions in specific group of [ITALIC:path operations].
[ITALIC: Different [CODE: dependencies] can be applied to different routers.
] These [CODE: dependencies] are run before the normal parameter dependencies. And normal dependencies are run too. They can be combined.
[ITALIC: Dependencies declared in a router are executed first, then the ones defined in ]path operation decorators[ITALIC:, and then the ones declared in normal parameters. They are all combined and executed.
] All this also supports using [CODE: Security] with [CODE: scopes] in those [CODE: dependencies] parameters, for more advanced OAuth 2.0 security scenarios with scopes.
[ITALIC: New documentation about dependencies in ]path operation decorators[ITALIC:.
] New documentation about [dependencies in the [CODE: include]router()] method](https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/bigger-applications/#include-an-apirouter-with-a-prefix-tags-responses-and-dependencies).
[ITALIC: PR #235.
] Fix OpenAPI documentation of Starlette URL convertors. Specially useful when using [CODE: path] convertors, to take a whole path as a parameter, like [CODE: /some/url/{p:path}]. PR #234 by @euri10.
[ITALIC: Make default parameter utilities exported from [CODE: fastapi] be functions instead of classes (the new functions return instances of those classes). To be able to override the return types and fix [CODE: mypy] errors in FastAPI's users' code. Applies to [CODE: Path], [CODE: Query], [CODE: Header], [CODE: Cookie], [CODE: Body], [CODE: Form], [CODE: File], [CODE: Depends], and [CODE: Security]. PR #226 and PR #231.
] Separate development scripts [CODE: test.sh], [CODE: lint.sh], and [CODE: format.sh]. PR #232.
- Re-enable [CODE: black] formatting checks for Python 3.7. PR #229 by @zamiramir.

