## Add [CODE: .gitignore]
If you are using [BOLD:Git] (you should), add a [CODE: .gitignore] file to exclude everything in your [CODE: .venv] from Git.
/// tip
If you used [[CODE: uv]](https://github.com/astral-sh/uv) to create the virtual environment, it already did this for you, you can skip this step.
///
/// tip
Do this [BOLD:once], right after you create the virtual environment.
///

[CODE[ITALIC:BLOCK]0: $ echo "[ITALIC:" > .venv/.gitignore...]

/// details | What that command means
] [CODE: echo "[ITALIC:"]: will "print" the text [CODE: ]] in the terminal (the next part changes that a bit)
[ITALIC: [CODE: >]: anything printed to the terminal by the command to the left of [CODE: >] should not be printed but instead written to the file that goes to the right of [CODE: >]
] [CODE: .gitignore]: the name of the file where the text should be written
And [CODE: [ITALIC:] for Git means "everything". So, it will ignore everything in the [CODE: .venv] directory.
That command will create a file [CODE: .gitignore] with the content:
[CODE[ITALIC:BLOCK]1: ]...]
///

