## Additional Response with [CODE: model]
You can pass to your [ITALIC:path operation decorators] a parameter [CODE: responses].
It receives a [CODE: dict]: the keys are status codes for each response (like [CODE: 200]), and the values are other [CODE: dict]s with the information for each of them.
Each of those response [CODE: dict]s can have a key [CODE: model], containing a Pydantic model, just like [CODE: response[ITALIC:model].
[BOLD:FastAPI] will take that model, generate its JSON Schema and include it in the correct place in OpenAPI.
For example, to declare another response with a status code [CODE: 404] and a Pydantic model [CODE: Message], you can write:
```python
@app.get("/items/{item]id}", response[ITALIC:model=Item, responses={404: {"model": Message}})
async def read]item(item[ITALIC:id: str):
return JSONResponse(status]code=404, content={"message": "Item not found"})
```
/// note
Keep in mind that you have to return the [CODE: JSONResponse] directly.
///
/// info
The [CODE: model] key is not part of OpenAPI.
[BOLD:FastAPI] will take the Pydantic model from there, generate the JSON Schema, and put it in the correct place.
The correct place is:
[ITALIC: In the key [CODE: content], that has as value another JSON object ([CODE: dict]) that contains:
] A key with the media type, e.g. [CODE: application/json], that contains as value another JSON object, that contains:
[ITALIC: A key [CODE: schema], that has as the value the JSON Schema from the model, here's the correct place.
] [BOLD:FastAPI] adds a reference here to the global JSON Schemas in another place in your OpenAPI instead of including it directly. This way, other applications and clients can use those JSON Schemas directly, provide better code generation tools, etc.
///
The generated responses in the OpenAPI for this [ITALIC:path operation] will be:
```JSON hl[ITALIC:lines="3-12"
{
"responses": {
"404": {
"description": "Additional Response",
"content": {
"application/json": {
"schema": {
"$ref": "#/components/schemas/Message"
}
}
}
},
"200": {
"description": "Successful Response",
