## Multiple Workers
You can start multiple workers with the [CODE: --workers] command line option:
//// tab | [CODE: fastapi]
If you use the [CODE: fastapi] command:

[CODE[ITALIC:BLOCK]0: $ fastapi run --worke...]

////
//// tab | [CODE: uvicorn]
If you prefer to use the [CODE: uvicorn] command directly:

[CODE[ITALIC:BLOCK]1: $ uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8080 --wo...]

////
The only new option here is [CODE: --workers] telling Uvicorn to start 4 worker processes.
You can also see that it shows the [BOLD:PID] of each process, [CODE: 27365] for the parent process (this is the [BOLD:process manager]) and one for each worker process: [CODE: 27368], [CODE: 27369], [CODE: 27370], and [CODE: 27367].

