### Include the custom docs
Now you can create the [ITALIC:path operations] for the custom docs.
You can reuse FastAPI's internal functions to create the HTML pages for the docs, and pass them the needed arguments:
[ITALIC: [CODE: openapi[ITALIC:url]: the URL where the HTML page for the docs can get the OpenAPI schema for your API. You can use here the attribute [CODE: app.openapi]url].
] [CODE: title]: the title of your API.
[ITALIC: [CODE: oauth2[ITALIC:redirect]url]: you can use [CODE: app.swagger[ITALIC:ui]oauth2[ITALIC:redirect]url] here to use the default.
] [CODE: swagger[ITALIC:js]url]: the URL where the HTML for your Swagger UI docs can get the [BOLD:JavaScript] file. This is the custom CDN URL.
[ITALIC: [CODE: swagger[ITALIC:css]url]: the URL where the HTML for your Swagger UI docs can get the [BOLD:CSS] file. This is the custom CDN URL.
And similarly for ReDoc...
```python
from fastapi.openapi.docs import (
get[ITALIC:redoc]html,
get[ITALIC:swagger]ui[ITALIC:html,
get]swagger[ITALIC:ui]oauth2[ITALIC:redirect]html,
)
@app.get("/docs", include[ITALIC:in]schema=False)
async def custom[ITALIC:swagger]ui[ITALIC:html():
return get]swagger[ITALIC:ui]html(
openapi[ITALIC:url=app.openapi]url,
title=app.title + " - Swagger UI",
oauth2[ITALIC:redirect]url=app.swagger[ITALIC:ui]oauth2[ITALIC:redirect]url,
swagger[ITALIC:js]url="https://unpkg.com/swagger-ui-dist@5/swagger-ui-bundle.js",
swagger[ITALIC:css]url="https://unpkg.com/swagger-ui-dist@5/swagger-ui.css",
)
@app.get(app.swagger[ITALIC:ui]oauth2[ITALIC:redirect]url, include[ITALIC:in]schema=False)
async def swagger[ITALIC:ui]redirect():
return get[ITALIC:swagger]ui[ITALIC:oauth2]redirect[ITALIC:html()
@app.get("/redoc", include]in[ITALIC:schema=False)
async def redoc]html():
return get[ITALIC:redoc]html(
openapi[ITALIC:url=app.openapi]url,
title=app.title + " - ReDoc",
redoc[ITALIC:js]url="https://unpkg.com/redoc@2/bundles/redoc.standalone.js",
)
```
/// tip
The ]path operation* for [CODE: swagger[ITALIC:ui]redirect] is a helper for when you use OAuth2.
If you integrate your API with an OAuth2 provider, you will be able to authenticate and come back to the API docs with the acquired credentials. And interact with it using the real OAuth2 authentication.
Swagger UI will handle it behind the scenes for you, but it needs this "redirect" helper.
///

