[Context: Middleware]

# Middleware
You can add middleware to [BOLD:FastAPI] applications.
A "middleware" is a function that works with every [BOLD:request] before it is processed by any specific [ITALIC:path operation]. And also with every [BOLD:response] before returning it.
[ITALIC: It takes each [BOLD:request] that comes to your application.
] It can then do something to that [BOLD:request] or run any needed code.
[ITALIC: Then it passes the [BOLD:request] to be processed by the rest of the application (by some ]path operation[ITALIC:).
] It then takes the [BOLD:response] generated by the application (by some [ITALIC:path operation]).
[ITALIC: It can do something to that [BOLD:response] or run any needed code.
] Then it returns the [BOLD:response].
/// note | Technical Details
If you have dependencies with [CODE: yield], the exit code will run [ITALIC:after] the middleware.
If there were any background tasks (covered in the Background Tasks section, you will see it later), they will run [ITALIC:after] all the middleware.
///

