[Context: Request Files > What is "Form Data"]

## What is "Form Data"
The way HTML forms ([CODE: ]) sends the data to the server normally uses a "special" encoding for that data, it's different from JSON.
[BOLD:FastAPI] will make sure to read that data from the right place instead of JSON.
/// note | Technical Details
Data from forms is normally encoded using the "media type" [CODE: application/x-www-form-urlencoded] when it doesn't include files.
But when the form includes files, it is encoded as [CODE: multipart/form-data]. If you use [CODE: File], [BOLD:FastAPI] will know it has to get the files from the correct part of the body.
If you want to read more about these encodings and form fields, head to the [MDN web docs for [CODE: POST]](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Methods/POST).
///
/// warning
You can declare multiple [CODE: File] and [CODE: Form] parameters in a [ITALIC:path operation], but you can't also declare [CODE: Body] fields that you expect to receive as JSON, as the request will have the body encoded using [CODE: multipart/form-data] instead of [CODE: application/json].
This is not a limitation of [BOLD:FastAPI], it's part of the HTTP protocol.
///

