## Technical Details
/// tip
If you are already using [BOLD:FastAPI] version [BOLD:0.99.0 or above], you can probably [BOLD:skip] these details.
They are more relevant for older versions, before OpenAPI 3.1.0 was available.
You can consider this a brief OpenAPI and JSON Schema [BOLD:history lesson]. 🤓
///
/// warning
These are very technical details about the standards [BOLD:JSON Schema] and [BOLD:OpenAPI].
If the ideas above already work for you, that might be enough, and you probably don't need these details, feel free to skip them.
///
Before OpenAPI 3.1.0, OpenAPI used an older and modified version of [BOLD:JSON Schema].
JSON Schema didn't have [CODE: examples], so OpenAPI added its own [CODE: example] field to its own modified version.
OpenAPI also added [CODE: example] and [CODE: examples] fields to other parts of the specification:
[ITALIC: [[CODE: Parameter Object] (in the specification)](https://github.com/OAI/OpenAPI-Specification/blob/main/versions/3.1.0.md#parameter-object) that was used by FastAPI's:
] [CODE: Path()]
[ITALIC: [CODE: Query()]
] [CODE: Header()]
[ITALIC: [CODE: Cookie()]
] [[CODE: Request Body Object], in the field [CODE: content], on the [CODE: Media Type Object] (in the specification)](https://github.com/OAI/OpenAPI-Specification/blob/main/versions/3.1.0.md#media-type-object) that was used by FastAPI's:
[ITALIC: [CODE: Body()]
] [CODE: File()]
