As SQLModel is based on SQLAlchemy, you can easily use [BOLD:any database supported] by SQLAlchemy (which makes them also supported by SQLModel), like:
[ITALIC: PostgreSQL
] MySQL
[ITALIC: SQLite
] Oracle
- Microsoft SQL Server, etc.
In this example, we'll use [BOLD:SQLite], because it uses a single file and Python has integrated support. So, you can copy this example and run it as is.
Later, for your production application, you might want to use a database server like [BOLD:PostgreSQL].
/// tip
There is an official project generator with [BOLD:FastAPI] and [BOLD:PostgreSQL] including a frontend and more tools: https://github.com/fastapi/full-stack-fastapi-template
///
This is a very simple and short tutorial, if you want to learn about databases in general, about SQL, or more advanced features, go to the SQLModel docs.

