## Hash and verify the passwords
Import the tools we need from [CODE: pwdlib].
Create a PasswordHash instance with recommended settings - it will be used for hashing and verifying passwords.
/// tip
pwdlib also supports the bcrypt hashing algorithm but does not include legacy algorithms - for working with outdated hashes, it is recommended to use the passlib library.
For example, you could use it to read and verify passwords generated by another system (like Django) but hash any new passwords with a different algorithm like Argon2 or Bcrypt.
And be compatible with all of them at the same time.
///
Create a utility function to hash a password coming from the user.
And another utility to verify if a received password matches the hash stored.
And another one to authenticate and return a user.
```python
from pwdlib import PasswordHash
from pydantic import BaseModel
password[ITALIC:hash = PasswordHash.recommended()

DUMMY]HASH = password[ITALIC:hash.hash("dummypassword")

def verify]password(plain[ITALIC:password, hashed]password):
return password[ITALIC:hash.verify(plain]password, hashed[ITALIC:password)
def get]password[ITALIC:hash(password):
return password]hash.hash(password)
def authenticate[ITALIC:user(fake]db, username: str, password: str):
user = get[ITALIC:user(fake]db, username)
if not user:
verify[ITALIC:password(password, DUMMY]HASH)
return False
if not verify[ITALIC:password(password, user.hashed]password):
return False
return user
```
When [CODE: authenticate[ITALIC:user] is called with a username that doesn't exist in the database, we still run [CODE: verify]password] against a dummy hash.
This ensures the endpoint takes roughly the same amount of time to respond whether the username is valid or not, preventing [BOLD:timing attacks] that could be used to enumerate existing usernames.
/// note
If you check the new (fake) database [CODE: fake[ITALIC:users]db], you will see how the hashed password looks like now: [CODE: "$argon2id$v=19$m=65536,t=3,p=4$wagCPXjifgvUFBzq4hqe3w$CYaIb8sB+wtD+Vu/P4uod1+Qof8h+1g7bbDlBID48Rc"].
///

