## Dependency tree and scopes
Let's review again this dependency tree and the scopes.
As the [CODE: get[ITALIC:current]active[ITALIC:user] dependency has as a sub-dependency on [CODE: get]current[ITALIC:user], the scope [CODE: "me"] declared at [CODE: get]current[ITALIC:active]user] will be included in the list of required scopes in the [CODE: security[ITALIC:scopes.scopes] passed to [CODE: get]current[ITALIC:user].
The [ITALIC:path operation] itself also declares a scope, [CODE: "items"], so this will also be in the list of [CODE: security]scopes.scopes] passed to [CODE: get[ITALIC:current]user].
Here's how the hierarchy of dependencies and scopes looks like:
[ITALIC: The ]path operation[ITALIC: [CODE: read[ITALIC:own]items] has:
] Required scopes [CODE: ["items"]] with the dependency:
[ITALIC: [CODE: get[ITALIC:current]active[ITALIC:user]:
] The dependency function [CODE: get]current[ITALIC:active]user] has:
[ITALIC: Required scopes [CODE: ["me"]] with the dependency:
] [CODE: get[ITALIC:current]user]:
[ITALIC: The dependency function [CODE: get[ITALIC:current]user] has:
] No scopes required by itself.
[ITALIC: A dependency using [CODE: oauth2[ITALIC:scheme].
] A [CODE: security]scopes] parameter of type [CODE: SecurityScopes]:
[ITALIC: This [CODE: security[ITALIC:scopes] parameter has a property [CODE: scopes] with a [CODE: list] containing all these scopes declared above, so:
] [CODE: security]scopes.scopes] will contain [CODE: ["me", "items"]] for the [ITALIC:path operation] [CODE: read[ITALIC:own]items].
[ITALIC: [CODE: security[ITALIC:scopes.scopes] will contain [CODE: ["me"]] for the ]path operation[ITALIC: [CODE: read]users[ITALIC:me], because it is declared in the dependency [CODE: get]current[ITALIC:active]user].
] [CODE: security[ITALIC:scopes.scopes] will contain [CODE: []] (nothing) for the [ITALIC:path operation] [CODE: read]system[ITALIC:status], because it didn't declare any [CODE: Security] with [CODE: scopes], and its dependency, [CODE: get]current[ITALIC:user], doesn't declare any [CODE: scopes] either.
/// tip
The important and "magic" thing here is that [CODE: get]current_user] will have a different list of [CODE: scopes] to check for each [ITALIC:path operation].
All depending on the [CODE: scopes] declared in each [ITALIC:path operation] and each dependency in the dependency tree for that specific [ITALIC:path operation].
